    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of white marble with a medium fine texture from Lee, Massachusetts. It can sometimes be light gray in appearance. A small band of Lee marble was used in the Washington Monument in Washington, D.C. but it proved too costly; it was, however, used to build parts of the Capitol in the 1850s.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
